    > * values from 0 to 32767, except for values from 147 to 162, are marked as Specification Required;
    > * values from 32768 to 65000 are marked as First-Come First-Served;
    > * values from 147 to 162, and from 65000 to 65535 are marked as Private Use.

This is much clearer. I'll use that.

> This is much clearer. I'll use that.

Or

- values from 0 to 146, and from 163 to 32767, are marked as Specification Required;
- values from 32768 to 65000 are marked as First-Come First-Served;
- values from 147 to 162, and from 65000 to 65535 are marked as Private Use.

I'd leave that in, because not *all* the values in that range are marked as Specification Required.

Perhaps:

* values from 0 to 32767, except for values from 147 to 162, are marked as Specification Required;
* values from 147 to 162 are marked as Private Use;
* values from 32768 to 65000 are marked as First-Come First-Served;
* values from 65000 to 65535 are marked as Private Use.

Alternatively, we could do

* values from 0 to 32767, except for values from 147 to 162, are marked as Specification Required;
* values from 32768 to 65000 are marked as First-Come First-Served;
* values from 147 to 162, and from 65000 to 65535 are marked as Private Use.
